<section>
<title></title>

<para>
There are three basic scenarios for writing about (R) code
within a document.
These are:
<ul>
<li>([<xml:tag>r:code</xml:tag>]) we issue an command (interactively) and examine the output and explain how this leads us to the next command
which leads to the next <xml:tag>r:code</xml:tag> element;</li>
<li>(<xml:tag>r:commands</xml:tag>) we issue a collection of commands and examine the output of each;</li>
<li>(<xml:tag>r:code</xml:tag>)  we issue several commands, but we are only interested in the output of the
last one; the preceding ones are intermediate computations that do not change which commands we perform next</li>
</ul>

</para>
