<section>
<title>Customizing the appearance of the output</title>

<para>
When we insert the result of a computation in R into our 
dynamic document, we often have strong ideas about how it should appear.
Frequency tables should be actual tables; similarly matrices  and data frames should
be two-way tables; vectors should appear in a particular form.
The <omg:pkg>XDynDocs</omg:pkg> package facilitates customizing the appearance in
several (4) ways:

<ol>
<li> use the default verbatim output from R</li>
<li> provide a method for the existing class </li>
<li> return the object as an instance of a new class and provide a method for that class</li>
<li> provide a template for the output and allow R and <omg:pkg>XDynDocs</omg:pkg>to try to extrapolate
  that patter. This is best done with a table.</li>
</ol>

